### Render Create Schedule Form Atom (JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/calcom/cal.com/blob/main/docs/platform/atoms/create-schedule.mdx

Illustrates how to use the CreateScheduleForm atom, a headless component for integrating the schedule creation form directly into your UI. This approach offers full flexibility in layout and styling, with props available for custom class names and callbacks.

```javascript
import { CreateScheduleForm } from "@calcom/atoms";

export default function CreateScheduleForm() {
  return (
    <>
      <CreateScheduleForm
        customClassNames={{
          atomsWrapper: "border-black border w-[500px] my-10 mx-5 rounded-md px-5 py-5",
          buttons: {
            continue: "bg-red-400 border-none",
            container: "justify-start",
          },
        }}
      />
    </>
  )
}
```

